Module com.example.pingpong
Package com.example.pingpong.Model

Class GameSettings

java.lang.Object
com.example.pingpong.Model.GameSettings
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class GameSettings extends Object implements Serializable
Stores and manages all settings for a Ping-Pong game. This includes player names, scores, and various game configurations such as ball speed, racket dimensions, and the winning score criteria.

    • GameSettings

      public GameSettings(String player1Name, String player2Name, int player1Score, int player2Score, double gameSpeed, double speedIncreaseFrequency, double racketWidth, double racketLength, int winningScore, int racketSize, int racketThickness)
      Constructs a new GameSettings object with initial values for all game settings.
      Parameters:
      player1Name - Name of player 1.
      player2Name - Name of player 2.
      player1Score - Initial score of player 1.
      player2Score - Initial score of player 2.
      gameSpeed - Initial speed of the game ball.
      speedIncreaseFrequency - Rate at which the game ball's speed increases.
      racketWidth - Width of the player's racket.
      racketLength - Length of the player's racket.
      winningScore - Score required to win the game.
      racketSize - Size category of the racket.
      racketThickness - Thickness of the racket.
